RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 47. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $750 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CROSS CLAIM tracked the pace from the three path, then was moving up on the turn to take command in the early stretch, then kicked clear in late stretch and held on well to prove best in the end. MORO PRINCESS set the pace along the inside, led gamely throughout the turn then gave way to an outer rival in the late stretch and was best for second. LOCKSMITH LEAH chased the pace while three wide, was moving up on the turn to rally in the stretch and was closing well in the end. NOMOROTHAT pressed the pace while two wide, was in a hard drive throughout the turn, then flattened out in late stretch. TERE'SDRAMAQUEEN trailed behind the field early, then rallied in the late stretch while two wide and was no threat. SHACK IT TO ME chased the pace from the inside, then rallied on the turn and needed more in the end. EXPECT LAVENDER broke awkwardly at the start, then was distanced early, rallied on the turn and passed tired rivals in the end. DOC'S BUD chased the pace while four wide, then rallied on the turn and into the early stretch, was used up and tired in late stretch. MAGICAL GOLD raced in the middle of the field while two wide, then bid on the turn and flattened out in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 7 1/2F Turf CR: 87. Claiming Purse 23000. (PLUS UP TO $4,600 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 23, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile. If the race is for two year olds, it will be run at Seven Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUMMER CAT coaxed shortly away from the gate to take control of the pace into the first turn, set a well measured, unchallenged pace, responded when called upon at the top of the lane and kept giving in a well handled ride. ENDLESS ROMANCE rated just off the early pace, lost some position down the backside when several rivals made early moves, kept rail position saving ground and rallied well up the fence in the stretch. STREET TAPPER tracked the leader from the rail to the far turn while well positioned, waited for racing room through the final bend, angled out for the drive and finished willingly. CARPE HORSESHOE stalked the pace from three wide while hard held, loomed up three wide in the turn and lacked a closing kick. QUINN ELLA unhurried early to be at the back, made a bold middle move to mount a wide bid in the far turn and flattened out coming home. DEL MAR DRAMA well placed in striking distance of the leader, moved up to challenge in the turn and evened out. DADDYMADEMEDOIT prompted the pace from the rail through both turns and weakened in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 5 1 1/16M Turf CR: 98. Claiming Purse 23000. (PLUS UP TO $4,600 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE AT A MILE OR OVER ON THE TURF SINCE FEBRUARY 23, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or O ver Since April 23, 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PARROT HEAD was well rated along the inside down the backstretch, was gaining ground gamely throughout the far turn to vie with an inner trio at the quarter marker, then inched away to duel with an inner rival in the late stretch and was able kick clear and be up at the wire. BIG COUNTRY tracked the pace from the inside down the backstretch close behind the leaders, was moving up on the second turn to vie for the lead, bumped an inner rival, continued to bid gamely down lane while battling with an outer rival and was out finished in the end. KAZAN (IRE) was unhurried early, then settled in the two path, bid on the far turn to rally in the late stretch and closed gamely for show. DRIVEHAPPY chased the pace down the backstretch while two to three wide, was urging on the far turn to rally from the five path in the late stretch and closed well in the end. JUST A IRISH LAD settled along the inside throughout the first three quarters, was urging on the far turn to bid in the early stretch, was denied room, then was clear in the late stretch to close willingly in the end. RANDELLO set the pace into the first turn and onto the backstretch, was in a long drive throughout the far turn to try to maintain the lead but gave way in the end. GORDON ANTHONY was bumped at the start, then stalked the pace early under a hard drive, then flattened out on the far turn. CITY LEGEND broke outwardly and bumped rival, then pressed the pace from the two path down the backstretch and into the far turn, vied for the lead at the quarter marker, was in tight, then bumped and gave way in the stretch. There was a STEWARD'S INQUIRY and JOCKEY'S OBJECTION following the race. The rider of BIG COUNTRY claimed foul against the rider of PARROT HEAD for interference leaving the second turn. After reviewing the replay, no change was made to the order of finish.
